	<div class="commentcontent">
		<p>@#6 ZAREN</p>

<p>The issue isn't in the 'ease' of transcoding an iTunes aac/mp3 or other lossy music codec to another -- its in the loss of fidelity that you get when resampling.</p>

<p>It might be fun for kids stuff, but the artifacting makes most of the stuff i listen to unlistenable -- blips and beeps, whooshes, frequency ranges cut off, etc</p>

<p><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transcode" rel="nofollow">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transcode</a></p>

