<p>Keep in mind that neither Wal*Mart nor MLB have a focus on the supply of media. When their DRM systems go away you are, pretty much screwed. If Cupertino falls into the ocean tomorrow, you'll still be able to play, transfer, burn whatever media you bought.</p>

<p>Note that I'm no fan of DRM, I agree that we'd be better off without it (as does Apple) -- but without it we'd have no iTunes Store, no Amazon MP3's, etc. etc.</p>
